    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-11-18</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-02-21T20:59:34Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>End Pensions in Congress Act or EPIC Act - Amends the Civil Service Retirement System (CSRS) and the Federal Employees' Retirement System (FERS) to exclude Members of Congress, except the Vice President, from further CSRS and FERS retirement coverage.</p> <p>Prohibits further government contributions or deductions from such Member's basic pay for deposit in the Treasury to the credit of the Civil Service Retirement and Disability Fund.</p> <p>States that nothing in this Act shall: (1) be considered to nullify, modify, or otherwise affect any right, entitlement, or benefit under CSRS for any Member covering any period before the enactment of this Act; or (2) affect the eligibility of a Member to participate in the Thrift Savings Plan (TSP) in accordance with otherwise applicable law.</p> <p>Allows Members covered by such exclusion, within 90 days after enactment of this Act, to elect to remain subject to CSRS or FERS, as the case may be.</p> <p><br /> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
